  "decision": "The strict meaning-v2 null result (0/4 in every one of E619, E620, and this E625 control/treatment run across two seeds) replicates and is seed-robust: this decode-time role-bias lever alone never clears required-slot coverage. The direction of the fidelity/validity/reward benefit and the component-recall cost also replicate at seed=1, with larger magnitude than at seed=0. The required-placeholder-missing record count is seed-sensitive (3/4 at seed0 vs 2/4 at seed1 for the treatment arm) and structural_similarity's sign flips between seeds, so neither should be treated as a stable per-seed point estimate without a multi-seed mean. Retain E615's role bias as a decode-time default candidate (magnitude of benefit confirmed, not seed-fragile), but the required-slot/strict-meaning gap itself needs a genuinely different lever -- a decode-time bias that floors still-missing required slots the way semantic_plan_margin_decode_weight already floors still-required plan families -- not another duration or seed replay of the existing role-bias lever.",
